Author: Ian Cheug
Project_Summary: The project is focusing on the Internet of Things and what operating systems and browsers are used. The goal is to display some images and graphics.
Recommendations: I suggest giving more background information on the IoT as well as provide the code/documentation needed in order to create the graphs.

Author: Shafqat Mashrakey
Project_Summary: This project develops a password checking web app using gameplay elements to see if making security education interactive improves the adoption of strong, unique passwords.
Recommendations: I suggest providing the source code for the implementations. Also providing feedback of your experience. Any challenges or recommendations for others who may attempt to replicate this.

Author: Paulo Muniz
Project_Summary: This project explores the impact of different web development frameworks on developer productivity and project outcomes. By analyzing Angular, React, and Vue, we aim to provide insights into their performance, developer experience, and scalability.
Recommendations: Everything seems well put together and thorough. Great job.

Author: Eric Miguel
Project_Summary: The project aims to review different frameworks and compares them to provide details for those deciding on which framework to use for their future implementations.
Recommendations: No recommendations, everything was very well documented. Enjoyed looking over your project.

Author: Q Thompson
Project_Summary: An API or Application programming interface is a set of rules or protocols that let software applications communicate with each other to exchange data, features, and functionality. The purpose of this Project is to demonstrate different APIs and explain the complexities of each one and what the security risk is for each type of API.
Recommendations: I suggest adding instructions to implement these APIs, so others can follow your steps. Also, maybe talk about your experience with the project, your recommendations.
